### 1. Login (Admin) - run this first
# NOTE: You must update the user's role to 'Admin' in the DB first:
#   UPDATE users SET role = 'Admin' WHERE email = 'test.admin@example.com';

# @name login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test1234@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Create matc
# @name createMatch
POST http://localhost:8080/api/matches
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

{
    "game_id": "01KK1XJSBCH9WCNV6DY3VHD3S1"
}

### 3. Get user's matches - retrieves matches for authenticated user from JWT token
GET http://localhost:8080/api/matches/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### 3-1. Get user's matches with game_id query param
GET http://localhost:8080/api/matches/me?game_id=01KJ2XGG4QR2TBFVJDQW3K47T6
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### 4. Get specific match
GET http://localhost:8080/api/matches/01KJJ0WJMJNSGT3KYTHC38WGHT
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### 4-1. Get specific match which is not belongs to the authenticated user - should return 403
GET http://localhost:8080/api/matches/01KJ2XH1QAA1JH9CSWC3W86ZE6
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### 4-2. Resign from match
POST http://localhost:8080/api/matches/{{createMatch.response.body.id}}/resign
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}

### 5. Delete match (Admin only) - uses id from createMatch response
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/matches/{{createMatch.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access_token}}
